commit.message:
Provide a source code for binary elf

After an inspection with command strace, confirmed by binary size comparison,
I am sure that the source code is true.c (/bin/true) from coreutils-5.2.1,
under GPL-2+.

As suggested by @jbj, the source code was put in tests/src/. After a test,
I confirm it is fine for Debian.

This PR closes: #2

commit.message:
Fix getopt use in tools

This fixes https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=716387,
where it was reported that `textextract` would crash when invoked as
`textextract --`.

I removed the home-made special-casing for `--help`. It's not needed and
wasn't interacting right with `getopt`.
Release 1.1.10
Update release script to work for git, not svn

Standardize header guards

It was pointed out by https://lgtm.com that these were non-standard.

Set laola.pl not executable

This file is a library, not a program. Should make lintian happier.
Update web site location
Deprecation and security notices

Make a conversion explicit to suppress GCC warning

This implicit conversion gave a warning with `./configure --strict`.
Fix memset size

Suppress compiler warning in dbm_open call

This was caused by `dbm_open` missing a `const` in `ndbm.h`.

Check return value of snprintf in compose_name

This fixes a valid warning produced by GCC about truncated file names.
Put buffer size in interface of compose_name

/usr/bin/env perl -> /usr/bin/perl

A decade ago it might have been more reliable to use the `perl` in the
user's `PATH`, but these days we should have more luck with
`/usr/bin/perl`.

This removes the need for `70_fix interpreter path.patch`, which has
been carried by Debian.

Fix position of LDFLAGS in link commands

This applies `60_fix-LDFLAG-pos.patch`, which has been carried by
Debian.

From: Carlos Maddela <e7appew@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 23 Dec 2016 02:10:17 +1100
Subject: Fix position of LDFLAGS in link commands.

Description: Fix position of LDFLAGS in link commands.
 magicrescue builds without dupemap on Ubuntu because the
 conftest_link() function in the configure script fails to link
 with the gdbm library, due to the position of the LDFLAGS in
 the link command. Reordering fixes the problem.
 .
 The same fix is also required in the Makefile, otherwise the
 package will fail to build.

Correct the spelling of 'failure'

This applies `50_fix-failure-word.patch`, which has been carried by
Debian.

Description: fix the word 'faliure'.
Author: Joao Eriberto Mota Filho <eriberto@debian.org>
Last-Update: 2016-08-27

Add support for DESTDIR in Makefile.in

This should make it easier to package Magic Rescue in distributions. The
use of `DESTDIR` is described in
https://www.gnu.org/prep/standards/html_node/DESTDIR.html.

This removes the need for part of the second hunk of
`30_make-Makefile-compliant.patch` carried by Debian.

Remove unused `.o` rule in Makefile.in

This change should remove the need for the first hunk of
`30_make-Makefile-compliant.patch` carried by Debian.

Move struct definitions into recur.c

This makes sure all occurrences of `PATH_MAX` are below
`#include "util.h"`, which defines that constant on platforms where it's
not defined.

This should remove the need for `10_fix FTBFS Hurd.patch`, which has
been carried by Debian for Hurd compatibility.

Add SQLite recipe

Contributed through the Debian project by Eric Pozharski
Note in ChangeLog
Add contributed recipes for empathy and flv

Actually add the rar recipe

This was supposed to have been in the last release but somehow didn't
make it.

Add maintainer tools that were not in the tarballs

These tools were salvaged out of an old Subversion working copy. They
may or may not be in a working state.
